  <body>
    <section name="ParameterNumber">
      <p>Since Checkstyle 3.0</p>
      <subsection name="Description" id="Description">
        <p>
          Checks the number of parameters of a method or constructor.
        </p>
      </subsection>

      <subsection name="Properties" id="Properties">
        <div class="wrapper">
          <table>
            <tr>
              <th>name</th>
              <th>description</th>
              <th>type</th>
              <th>default value</th>
              <th>since</th>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td>ignoreAnnotatedBy</td>
              <td>Ignore methods and constructors annotated with the specified annotation(s).</td>
              <td><a href="../../property_types.html#String.5B.5D">String[]</a></td>
              <td><code>{}</code></td>
              <td>10.14.0</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td>ignoreOverriddenMethods</td>
              <td>Ignore number of parameters for methods with <code>@Override</code> annotation.</td>
              <td><a href="../../property_types.html#boolean">boolean</a></td>
              <td><code>false</code></td>
              <td>6.2</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td>max</td>
              <td>Specify the maximum number of parameters allowed.</td>
              <td><a href="../../property_types.html#int">int</a></td>
              <td><code>7</code></td>
              <td>3.0</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td>tokens</td>
              <td>tokens to check</td>
              <td>subset of tokens
                <a href="../../apidocs/com/puppycrawl/tools/checkstyle/api/TokenTypes.html#METHOD_DEF">
                    METHOD_DEF</a>
                , <a href="../../apidocs/com/puppycrawl/tools/checkstyle/api/TokenTypes.html#CTOR_DEF">
                    CTOR_DEF</a>
                  .
              </td>
              <td>
                <a href="../../apidocs/com/puppycrawl/tools/checkstyle/api/TokenTypes.html#METHOD_DEF">
                    METHOD_DEF</a>
                , <a href="../../apidocs/com/puppycrawl/tools/checkstyle/api/TokenTypes.html#CTOR_DEF">
                    CTOR_DEF</a>
                  .
              </td>
              <td>3.0</td>
            </tr>
          </table>
        </div>
      </subsection>

      <subsection name="Examples" id="Examples">
        <p id="Example1-config">
          To configure the check:
        </p>
        <source>
&lt;module name=&quot;Checker&quot;&gt;
  &lt;module name=&quot;TreeWalker&quot;&gt;
    &lt;module name=&quot;ParameterNumber&quot;/&gt;
  &lt;/module&gt;
&lt;/module&gt;
        </source>

        <p id="Example2-config">
          To configure the check to allow 10 parameters for a method:
        </p>
        <source>
&lt;module name=&quot;Checker&quot;&gt;
  &lt;module name=&quot;TreeWalker&quot;&gt;
    &lt;module name=&quot;ParameterNumber&quot;&gt;
      &lt;property name=&quot;max&quot; value=&quot;10&quot;/&gt;
      &lt;property name=&quot;tokens&quot; value=&quot;METHOD_DEF&quot;/&gt;
    &lt;/module&gt;
  &lt;/module&gt;
&lt;/module&gt;
        </source>
        <p>
          To configure the check to ignore number of parameters for methods with
          <code>@Override</code> or <code>@java.lang.Override annotation</code>.
        </p>
        <p id="Example3-config">
          Rationale: developer may need to override method with many parameters from
          3-rd party library.
          In this case developer has no control over number of parameters.
        </p>
        <source>
&lt;module name=&quot;Checker&quot;&gt;
  &lt;module name=&quot;TreeWalker&quot;&gt;
    &lt;module name=&quot;ParameterNumber&quot;&gt;
      &lt;property name=&quot;ignoreOverriddenMethods&quot; value=&quot;true&quot;/&gt;
    &lt;/module&gt;
  &lt;/module&gt;
&lt;/module&gt;
        </source>
        <p id="Example3-code">
          Java code example:
        </p>
        <source>
@Override
public void needsLotsOfParameters(int a,
    int b, int c, int d, int e, int f, int g, int h) {
    ...
}
        </source>
        <p id="Example4-config">
          To configure the check to ignore methods and constructors annotated with
          <code>JsonCreator</code> annotation:
        </p>
        <source>
&lt;module name=&quot;Checker&quot;&gt;
  &lt;module name=&quot;TreeWalker&quot;&gt;
    &lt;module name=&quot;ParameterNumber&quot;&gt;
      &lt;property name=&quot;ignoreAnnotatedBy&quot; value=&quot;JsonCreator&quot;/&gt;
    &lt;/module&gt;
  &lt;/module&gt;
&lt;/module&gt;
        </source>
        <p id="Example4-code"> Example:</p>
        <source>
class Example {
    @JsonCreator
    Example(int a, int b, int c, int d,
            int e, int f, int g, int h) {}

    @interface JsonCreator {}
}
        </source>
        <p>
          Fully qualified class name(s) can also specified in ignoreAnnotatedBy property.
          Note that when specifying annotation(s), only methods and constructors annotated with
          the exact specified annotation(s) will be ignored, any variation, even if it refers to
          the same annotation, will result in it being checked, and produce violation if any.
        </p>
        <p id="Example5-config">
          To configure the check to ignore methods and constructors annotated with
          <code>java.lang.Deprecated</code> annotation:
        </p>
        <source>
&lt;module name=&quot;Checker&quot;&gt;
  &lt;module name=&quot;TreeWalker&quot;&gt;
    &lt;module name=&quot;ParameterNumber&quot;&gt;
      &lt;property name=&quot;ignoreAnnotatedBy&quot; value=&quot;java.lang.Deprecated&quot;/&gt;
    &lt;/module&gt;
  &lt;/module&gt;
&lt;/module&gt;
        </source>
        <p id="Example5-code"> Example:</p>
        <source>
class Example {
    @java.lang.Deprecated
    void unchecked(int a, int b, int c, int d,
                  int e, int f, int g, int h) {}

    @Deprecated
    void checked(int a, int b, int c, int d, // violation, 'More than 7 parameters (found 8)'
                 int e, int f, int g, int h) {}
}
        </source>
      </subsection>

